# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# swarm-office server config. Copy to `.env` (gitignored) and fill in.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# F2b — OPTIONAL "M.IA gateway": an OpenAI-compatible chat-completions endpoint that
# becomes the NPC's brain. If these are unset the NPC falls back to scripted replies
# (F2a), so the app runs with no setup. SERVER-SIDE ONLY — the key never reaches the
# browser (spec §6). Loaded via process.loadEnvFile() in src/index.ts.

# Base URL up to and including /v1 (the client appends /chat/completions).
# MIA_GATEWAY_URL=https://your-host/route/v1

# Full Authorization header value, e.g. "Bearer <token>" or "Basic <base64>".
# MIA_GATEWAY_AUTH=Bearer your-token-here

# Model id as returned by GET {MIA_GATEWAY_URL}/models.
# MIA_GATEWAY_MODEL=your-model-id

# Set true ONLY when the endpoint serves a self-signed / hostname-mismatched cert
# (scopes rejectUnauthorized:false to the gateway Agent, never the whole process).
# MIA_GATEWAY_INSECURE_TLS=false
